replaceManager(address).details: Allows the owner or manager to replace the current manager

params.newManager: The address to give contract management rights.

transferOwnership(address).details: Allows the current owner to transfer control of the contract to a newOwner.

params.newOwner: The address to transfer ownership to.

allowance(address,address).details: Function to check the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender.

params._owner: address The address which owns the funds.
params._spender: address The address which will spend the funds.

allowance(address,address).return: A uint256 specifying the amount of tokens still available for the spender.

approve(address,uint256).details: Approve the passed address to spend the specified amount of tokens on behalf of msg.sender.    * Beware that changing an allowance with this method brings the risk that someone may use both the old and the new allowance by unfortunate transaction ordering. One possible solution to mitigate this race condition is to first reduce the spender's allowance to 0 and set the desired value afterwards: https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/issues/20#issuecomment-263524729

params._spender: The address which will spend the funds.
params._value: The amount of tokens to be spent.

balanceOf(address).details: Gets the balance of the specified address.

params._owner: The address to query the the balance of.

balanceOf(address).return: An uint256 representing the amount owned by the passed address.

decreaseApproval(address,uint256).details: Decrease the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender.    * approve should be called when allowed[_spender] == 0. To decrement allowed value is better to use this function to avoid 2 calls (and wait until the first transaction is mined) From MonolithDAO Token.sol

params._spender: The address which will spend the funds.
params._subtractedValue: The amount of tokens to decrease the allowance by.

finishMinting().details: Function to stop minting new tokens.
finishMinting().return: True if the operation was successful.

increaseApproval(address,uint256).details: Increase the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender.    * approve should be called when allowed[_spender] == 0. To increment allowed value is better to use this function to avoid 2 calls (and wait until the first transaction is mined) From MonolithDAO Token.sol

params._addedValue: The amount of tokens to increase the allowance by.
params._spender: The address which will spend the funds.

params._amount: The amount of tokens to mint.
params._to: The address that will receive the minted tokens.

mint(address,uint256).return: A boolean that indicates if the operation was successful.

div(uint256,uint256).details: Divides the dividend by divisor, returns the truncated quotient
div(uint256,uint256).return: quotient the quotient of the equation (e.g. dividend / divisor)

divideSafely(uint256,uint256).details: Divides the dividend by divisor, returns the quotient and remainder
divideSafely(uint256,uint256).return: quotient the quotient of the equation (e.g. dividend / divisor)remainder the remainder of the equation (e.g. dividend % divisor)

dividedBy(uint256,uint256).details: Divides the dividend by divisor, returns the truncated quotient
dividedBy(uint256,uint256).return: quotient the quotient of the equation (e.g. dividend / divisor)

isAtLeast(uint256,uint256).details: Determines whether a value is equal to or greater than another.
isAtLeast(uint256,uint256).return: isTrue whether a is less than b

isAtMost(uint256,uint256).details: Determines whether a value is equal to or less than another.
isAtMost(uint256,uint256).return: isTrue whether a is less than or equal to b

isGreaterThan(uint256,uint256).details: Determines whether a value is greater than another.
isGreaterThan(uint256,uint256).return: isTrue whether a is greater than b

isLessThan(uint256,uint256).details: Determines whether a value is less than another.
isLessThan(uint256,uint256).return: isTrue whether a is less than b

max(uint256,uint256).details: Returns the greater of two values.
max(uint256,uint256).return: result the greater of the two values

min(uint256,uint256).details: Returns the lesser of two values.
min(uint256,uint256).return: result the lesser of the two values

minus(uint256,uint256).details: Subtracts the minuend from the subtrahend, returns the difference

mul(uint256,uint256).details: Multiplies two factors, returns the product
mul(uint256,uint256).return: product the product of the equation (e.g. factorA * factorB)

plus(uint256,uint256).details: Adds two addends together, returns the sum
plus(uint256,uint256).return: sum the sum of the equation (e.g. addendA + addendB)

times(uint256,uint256).details: Multiplies two factors, returns the product
times(uint256,uint256).return: product the product of the equation (e.g. factorA * factorB)
